<subSubSection id="A7FBD702ACC3F140C4D5EE6FAFE73DE1" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5D28BAD808505059F3B81E303621884D" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B567E3D2D6262019A73DEC020AAD572A" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
The straight frontal ledge and short fore wings with dense microtrichia readily separate this species from other 
<taxonomicName id="21837A24C728EAC327349414150ABA31" class="Insecta" family="Platygastridae" genus="Pulchrisolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pulchrisolia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5162C4AF58C45C4794CBC3606820F64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Pulchrisolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C97D9A6D19400082B90852F874312DDC" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AB3B32A920BC7576291E82E847D71AFA" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31F12D47D625271B79CAEFE088138EED" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Named after the game reserve where the holotype was collected. Asante Sana is Swahili for &quot;thank you very much&quot;. The epithet is treated as a noun in apposition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
